writing down dreams when someone is trying to get good at remembering their dreams they are supposed to kkep a dream journal or sumthing like that but is their another way to do it such as just going through the dream in your head would it be as effective remembering your dreams will require some effort on your part but what your dreams can offer and tell you about yourself will be well worth it here are some tips in helping your dream recall before going to bed keep a clear mind tell yourself that i will remember my dream when i wake up this is actually a proven and effective way to help dream recall having too many thoughts on your mind can distract you from remembering your dream in the morning have a regular bedtime and wake up time make this your routine going to bed and waking up at a regular time every day aids in dream recollection avoid alcohol consumption and taking medication before going to bed these things may hinder you from remembering your dream eating fatty foods too close to bedtime can also divert bodily resources away from the brain and hinder dream recollection keep a pencil notebook or tape recorder next to your bed so that it will be within reach as soon as you wake up you want to make recording your dreams as easy a task as possible having a small lamp by your bedside is also a good idea should you wake up in the middle of the night and want to record your dream immediately do not get out of bed immediately upon waking from a dream lay still in your bed keeping your eyes closed and moving as little as possible wake up slowly and stay relax hold on to the feelings you have and let your mind wander to the images of what you have just dreamt were you frustrated terrified or happy write down as many details in your dream as you can no matter how minute or seemingly unimportant it may be do not judge the content or worry if it makes sense the idea is to get it down on paper so you can evaluate it later make it a habit that this is the first thing you do talking about your dreams to friends or participating in forums and chats also help you remember sometimes it may help to draw pictures a picture is worth a thousand words as the saying goes even if you are not an artist a simple drawing can help to jolt details of your dream Lucid dreaming Out-of-body experience Phaedo Social rule Milton H. Erickson Breastfeeding Jon Secada Philosophical skepticism Avenue Q The Shining (film) Fecal incontinence Scientology beliefs and practices Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Shaggy dog story Hypnosis Theory of conduct Unconscious mind 50 First Dates Time Out of Mind Diazepam Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Blood on the Tracks Fitz Hugh Ludlow Parsifal 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Dog training Procrastination Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Mnemonic Traditional animation The Amber Spyglass Hypoglycemia Dyslexia The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Derren Brown The Mother Stuttering Mattress Light pollution Ludwig Wittgenstein Hamster Sigmund Freud David Hume Extreme Programming The Lovely Bones Autism Marilyn Monroe Beetle in an Anthill Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Traumatic brain injury Miss Saigon Goodness and value theory Funeral Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans Pitaten Aikido Collecting fossils Drawing Socrates Summa Theologiae Frank Herbert The nature of God in Western theology Nutrition Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Stereoscopy Bong Meditation The Tracey Ullman Show shorts Stoicism Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Urinary incontinence Sukkot Veganism Insulin D__j__ vu Characters of The Sandman Datalore (TNG episode) Episodes of Lost (Season 2) The Star Wars Holiday Special John Berryman Slow Train Coming StarCraft: Uprising Brett Whiteley Social psychology USS Tunny (SS-282) A Course In Miracles Dave Matthews Band Hey Jude Naval mine The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan Erik Satie W.I.T.C.H. Arguments for and against drug prohibition 